replyContent: Hi Jason. Thanks for the feedback. You can actually do this - go into the parent / teacher area and tap the "Exclusions" button next to the child's name for whom you'd like to limit the tables available in "Fill the Gap" mode. Tap the "Fill the Gap" button and then tap any tables you want to exclude so they turn from orange to black. Thanks. Ian

I had a problem running this app under a child profile on my Nexus 7. I emailed the developer and was surprised to get a prompt and helpful responses - with several prompt follow up responses - including an offer to refund the purchase price. Given that the app costs only ¬£2 the level of customer service is brilliant. I have had slower / worst customer service for software costing over ¬£100.  One minor issue is that for an older child they have to tediously work through the kiddy levels (e.g. 2 to 5 times tables) in order to progress to the trickier levels - because of the way the reward system works. However, the developer has agreed to consider looking into an alternative system for a future release
replyContent: Hi Umer. As per our e-mail to you, we have tested this app with a restricted profile on a Nexus 7 and it works perfectly, as do all our other apps. If you can get back to us with the information I've requested in the e-mail we can look into it further to see why your device seems to be experiencing this issue. Many thanks. Ian. KeyStageFun.
